You must be able to explain some specifics about this infrastructure:

For every additional element, why you are adding it
 - A firewall for each server, we need to be able to manage what connections are allowed to hit the servers.
 - SSL certificates allows us to use HTTPS request and have a secure, encrypted connection with clients (plus SEO).
 - Monitoring clients to be able to get insight into our infrastructure.

What are firewalls for
 - Protect the servers from unwanted requests.
 - Isolate our internal servers from the internet so they only accept request that go through the load-balancer.

Why is the traffic served over HTTPS
 - Add encryption to requests.
 - Search Engine Optimization.
 - Have a secure connection with clients.

What monitoring is used for
 - We use one monitoring client to check and configure our firewall.
 - One for data insight like logs, performance, graphs, etc.
 - An uptime monitor so we can know if our app is running.

How the monitoring tool is collecting data
 - It uses many data points from the software and hardware of our servers to generate useful insight.
 - One example of it may be CPU and RAM usage, available space, database overview, running processes, etc.

Explain what to do if you want to monitor your web server QPS
 - We can use our monitoring tools to record hoy many query per second our application is handling.
 - We can also use NGINX at each server to know how many requests each server is receiving.


You must be able to explain what the issues are with this infrastructure:

Why terminating SSL at the load balancer level is an issue
 - It compromises security as requests are decrypted reaching the load-balancer, meaning packages are vulnerable to 
   being intercepted between internal servers.

Why having only one MySQL server capable of accepting writes is an issue
 - This means only heavy load all only one server is capable of writing to the database and become a bottleneck.
 - Also this means the slave nodes have to constantly update to catch up.
 - The main node may work as a SPOF.

Why having servers with all the same components (database, web server and application server) might be a problem
 - Security, if a server is hacked all other components within will be compromised as well.
 - If a case where we would need to scale up, we would have to add an entire new server with all of its components.
 Example:
 - If we needed another database node, we would have to add a whole new complete server, instead of just a database server.
